## Error Diagnosis

The error is:

```
keyword div(phiv,hU) is undefined in dictionary ".../system/fvSchemes/divSchemes"
```

The `shallowWaterFoam` solver requires a divergence scheme for `div(phiv,hU)`, but the current `fvSchemes` file only defines `div(phi,hU)`. The solver uses `phiv` (volume flux divided by cell face area, i.e., the velocity-based flux) rather than `phi` (the volume flow rate) for the convection of momentum `hU`.

Looking at the current `divSchemes`:

```
divSchemes
{
    default         none;
    div(phi,hU)     Gauss linearUpwind grad(hU);
}
```

The scheme `div(phi,hU)` does not exist in the context of `shallowWaterFoam` — the solver specifically looks for `div(phiv,hU)`.

## Solution

**Modify `system/fvSchemes`** to define the correct divergence scheme keyword that `shallowWaterFoam` expects. Add/replace the entry:

```
divSchemes
{
    default         none;
    div(phiv,hU)    Gauss linearUpwind grad(hU);
}
```

Specifically, change `div(phi,hU)` to `div(phiv,hU)`. The rest of the scheme settings (`Gauss linearUpwind grad(hU)`) appear correct based on the squareBump tutorial reference.

Additionally, reviewing the other divergence schemes in the file, `div(phi,h)` is also commonly needed by `shallowWaterFoam` since it solves for `h`. To be safe, you may want to include both:

```
divSchemes
{
    default         none;
    div(phiv,hU)    Gauss linearUpwind grad(hU);
    div(phi,h)      Gauss upwind;
}
```

But at minimum, the `div(phiv,hU)` entry must be present. The key fix is simply renaming the keyword from `div(phi,hU)` to `div(phiv,hU)` to match what the solver actually requests.

